Usage: createStairwayBoundary [-help] -dx <val> -dy <val>
                              [-growNeighborPtnDir {x y}] -ptn <string>
                              -step <nr> {-corner {LL LR UL UR} | -vertex <integer>}

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
-corner {LL LR UL UR}     # Specifies partition corner where a stairway will be
                          # created. (enum, optional)
-dx <val>                 # Specifies step width. (float, required)
-dy <val>                 # Specifies step height. (float, required)
-growNeighborPtnDir {x y} # Affected neighbor partition will be derived based
                          # on the specified direction of the target partition.
                          # if this option is not specified, NO abutted
                          # partition will be grown. (enum, optional)
-ptn <string>             # Specifies name of the target partition.
                          # (string, required)
-step <nr>                # Specifies how many steps in the created stairway.
                          # (int, required)
-vertex <integer>         # Specifies partion vertex where stairway will be
                          # created. Starting from lower left corner of a
                          # partition clock wise. The first vertex is number 0.
                          # A vertex number can be negative where corner
                          # numbering starts at 0 from the lower left corner of
                          # a partion counter clock-wise. (int, optional)